    &lt;Title&gt;Bud Flanagan Out Patients&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Sandra Johnstone&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I have been a patient of BFOP for nearly 19 years after being diagnosed with CLL in 2000.  I have visited the Hospital over 300 times!!  And although it has been an expensive journey for me, lost my job, lone parent, parking/petrol costing me a fortune (did publicity for Macmillan in 2007, nothing changed until I became a pensioner) I can only say that this department has saved my life.  The consultants treat you as a person, not a number, very rare these days.  I have seen 3 important members of BFOP retire, one consultant still emails me! But also have a wonderful caring “workaholic” consultant.  Also made many friends of patients, some come, and unfortunately some go.  Have had 3 trial drugs. Of course my life is on a roller coaster (and has been hard also for my now adult children too) and would be lovely to live a “normal” life, but I am so appreciative that I get all this treatment from the NHS... well I have paid my contributions too!!    Am now waiting to be put on a so-called miracle drug... have 3 very young grandchildren and want to see them grow up for as long as I can xxx&lt;/CommentText&gt;
